annotationA: Chorion protein 36 (Cp36) is an abundant structural protein of the eggshell whose expression is enhanced by gene amplification in ovarian follicle cells. Cp36 is essential for fertility and for endochorion integrity
annotationB: CG4009, isoform B; Peroxidase activity; heme binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: response to oxidative stress; oxidation-reduction process
